<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   21 March 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> LATIN AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> SURINAME </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Liberation Front' Seizes Afobaka Hydroelectric Plant </TI></H3>
<H4>   Takes Workers as Hostages </H4>
<F P=102> PA2203131094 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2343 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2203131094 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Hague, 21 Mar (EFE) -- The Dutch news agency ANP 
in Paramaribo has reported that members of a guerrilla group 
seized the hydroelectric plant in Afobaka hours ago and they are 
currently holding 30 hostages. 
  According to an unidentified spokesman of the group called 
the "Liberation Front of Suriname," access roads to the 
hydroelectric plant have been mined in a 7-km radius. The 
hydroelectric dam supplies energy to the country's capital, 
located 100 km to the north. 
  According to ANP, the guerrilla group is holding 30 
employees 
of Suralco, a bauxite company, hostage and they are demanding a 
"decentralization of power" and the resignation of the 
Surinamese Government. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

