<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   28 March 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Regional Guerrilla Activities Through 23 March </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2403201694 </F>
<F P=103> PA2403201694 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on regional guerrilla activities monitored through 23 
March. 
<H5>  Colombia </H5>
  In the early morning of 15 March, presumed FARC members 
dynamited a police roadblock near the 2 km marker of the 
Southern Highway in Neiva, Huila Department. No casualties were 
reported. (Santa Fe de Bogota EL TIEMPO in Spanish 17 Mar 94 p 
9A) 
  On 19 March, FARC kidnapped a doctor and a shopkeeper in 
Sabanas de Pedro, a rural area in Los Palmitos, Sucre 
Department, where 18 people have been kidnapped so far in 1994. 
Three FARC guerrillas died during a confrontation with the 
Narino Battalion troops in southern Bolivar Department on 19 
March. A member of the National Liberation Army (ELN) was 
killed in Rionegro, Santander Department. An ELN guerrilla was 
killed in a confrontation with the anti- guerrilla Granaderos 
Battalion in Campamento, northern Antioquia. Two soldiers were 
injured in a confrontation with FARC members in the rural area 
of Turbo in Uraba, Antioquia Department. (Santa Fe de Bogota EL 
TIEMPO in Spanish 21 Mar 94 p 8A) 
  On 22 March, 60 Socialist Renewal Movement guerrillas 
promised in Cali to demobilize and turn in their weapons. On 23 
March, they will move from Valle del Cauca, Narino, and Tolima 
to the peace camp in Flor del Monte. Rebels set off explosives 
in the police station of Angostura, northern Antioquia 
Department, killing two policemen. (Santa Fe de Bogota 
Inravision Television Cadena 1 in Spanish 0130 GMT 22 Mar 94) 
<H5>  Guatemala </H5>
  Presumed guerrillas on 16 March kidnapped the drivers of two 
oil tankers on a highway between Tucan and La Ceiba, Peten 
Department. (Guatemala City El GRAFICO in Spanish 17 Mar 94 p 2) 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

