<H3> <TI>   Security Tightened Around Would-Be Sidqi Assassins' Homes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2403154494 Cairo AL-WAFD in Arabic 21 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC2403154494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-WAFD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Najwa 'Abd-al-'Aziz] </F>
  [Text] The Interior Ministry yesterday started to reinforce 
the al-Qalyubiyah security agencies with "commandos" and threw 
tightened security cordons around the area of al-Khankah. 
  Strict security measures were taken around the homes of 
three 
extremists sentenced in connection with the attempt to kill 
Prime Minister Dr. 'Atif Sidqi. The convicts are Salah Sulayman 
and Tariq Hasan al-Fahl, sentenced to death, and Muhammad 
Khalil, sentenced to life with hard labor. 
  The security agencies stepped up search campaigns in the 
underground terminals and on roads in the area of al-Marj to 
prevent weapons and explosives from reaching the families of the 
three convicts through extremist group members. 

</TEXT>

