<H3> <TI>   Bank Bombs Sourced in Afghanistan, China, Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1903101294 Cairo AL-WAFD in Arabic 13 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC1903101294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-WAFD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Muhammad 'Abd-al-Fattah] </F>
  [Text] Investigations carried out by the State Security 
[Prosecution Office] in the case involving recent bank bombings 
indicate that deceased terrorist Yasir Zaki collaborated with 
defendants held in connection with this case, providing them 
with explosives before his death. 
  An official security source says that the electric circuits 
[al- dawa'ir al-kahraba'iyah] found at the bomb sites were made 
in Afghanistan, the timers in China, and the explosive material 
in Russia. According to the same source, police have discovered 
the hideouts of key terrorists and started a search in six 
governorates to arrest them. 

