<F P=100> NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> INDIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Home Ministry Releases Report on Terrorism in Kashmir </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2303101094 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2303101094 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Home Ministry's annual report for the year 
1993-94 says that the unabated aiding and abetting of terrrorism 
from across the border in Jammu and Kashmir [J and K] is coupled 
with growing infiltration of foreign nationals and mercenaries 
into the state. It said efforts were made to destabilize and 
destroy the democratic institutions by the fear of the gun and 
to change the demographic profile in parts of the state. The 
report also regretted that new trend was observed in the form of 
efforts to spread violence in the Jammu region, particularly to 
Doda District. Referring to the government's efforts to expose 
the false propaganda and the role of Pakistan in fuelling 
terrorism in the state, the report gives details of several 
initiatives launched during the year for accelerating 
development and economic activity in J and K. 
  On Punjab, the report observed that the situation there has 
shown a marked inprovement. The report also highlighted various 
steps taken by the government to curb communal violence in 
general and that which was related to the Ayodhya incident. 
Other steps taken by the government on the Ayodhya issue were 
also given in the report. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

