<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Wounded in 9 Mar Assassination Attempt </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2203164394 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 21 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM2203164394 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Governors of Ninawa and Babil </F>
Dismissed After Wave of Disturbances Over High Cost of Living"] 
  [Excerpt] Amman, London, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- [passage 
omitted] The Iraqi "Free Revolutionary Officers Movement" 
[IFROM] has revealed that there was an attempt to assassinate 
Iraqi Defense Minister 'Ali Hasan al-Majid 9 March. 
  In a statement, a copy of which was received by AL-SHARQ 
AL-AWSAT yesterday, the movement said that one of its units 
carried out the operation, in which 'Ali Hasan al-Majid 
sustained leg and hand injuries and his aide, Police Major Salih 
Arjah, and two guards were killed outside the Iraqi defense 
minister's home in Baghdad. 
  The statement said that the nucleus of the IFROM was formed 
before Saddam Husayn's forces invaded Kuwait and that it 
includes a group of senior officers and soldiers, including 
prominent officers in important positions. 
  The statement added that 136 IFROM officers and soldiers 
have 
been martyred in operations against the regime's forces and that 
in the first two months of this year it distributed thousands of 
antiregime leaflets in the camps of al-Rashid, al-Taji, 
al-Suwayrah, al-Rashidiyah, and Khan Bani-Sa'id. 
  It urged the Iraqi opposition forces to unite and end their 
political rivalry, and it stressed that the desired change 
should emanate from within Iraq and from within the Armed Forces. 
  It also said that it strives for a truly democratic regime 
in 
Iraq, for Iraq's return to the Arab fold, for fraternal and 
good-neighborly relations with the neighboring states, and for 
the reconstruction of a strong Iraqi economy. 

</TEXT>

