<F P=103> TA2403200994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [See Selected Video Reports section for TV footage of </F>
incident] 
  [Text] Major General Sha'ul Mufaz, commander of the IDF 
[Israel Defense Forces] forces in Judaea and Samaria, said this 
evening that the three terrorists killed by the security forces 
in Hebron belonged to one of the most prominent terror squads in 
the territories. Maj. Gen. Mufaz told correspondents that so 
far three bodies were found in the building in which the 
terrorists barricaded themselves. Mufaz says these terrorists 
were involved in a long series of attacks, including the murder 
of Mordekhay and Shalom Lapid in Hebron, and the murder of 
Avraham Zarbiv near the Cave of the Patriarchs. 
  Maj. Gen. Mufaz said that following the operation in Hebron 
only 10 Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] and Islamic Jihad 
terrorists remain operating in Judaea and Samaria. Mufaz added 
that the Hebron operation was made possible by strenuous Shin 
Bet efforts. According to Mufaz the house in which the 
terrorists hid served as a storehouse and a launch pad for Hamas 
terror acts. 

</TEXT>

