<F P=102> TA2103175394 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1730 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2103175394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Here is a special news report following a terrorist 
attack in the Binyamin area. There was a shooting attack near 
the settlement of 'Ateret. According to initial reports, two 
Egged bus passengers were seriously injured. Our correspondent 
in the territories Golan Yokhpaz reports from the studio: 
  There was a shooting attack near the settlement of 'Ateret, 
which is situated north of Jerusalem. Apparently two Israelis 
were seriously injured and three others were also wounded, 
although their condition remains unclear. The Israelis were hit 
by gunfire directed at an Egged No. 468 bus which drove by the 
settlement of 'Ateret in the Binyamin area on the Bi'r Zayt 
bypass. The bus, was travelling from Jerusalem to Tel Aviv and 
picking up passengers from settlements in the Binyamin area. 
Seven Israeli ambulances are currently racing to the scene in 
order to evacuate the wounded, apparently to Hadassah-'En Kerem 
Hospital in Jerusalem. Large Army forces are also making their 
way to the scene of the attack in order to treat the wounded and 
close off the site. 
  We have just received an update on the condition of the 
wounded: five are currently receiving first aid at the scene and 
initial reports indicate that two of the wounded are in serious 
condition and will soon be evacuated to hospital. 

</TEXT>

