Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] George Habash's Popular Front for the 
Liberation of Palestine [PFLP] has assumed responsibility for 
the terrorist attack on a bus near the settlement of 'Ateret 
yesterday. Two Israeli citizens were injured in the attack. 
Here is a report by our correspondent in the territories Golan 
Yokhpaz: 
  A leaflet signed by PFLP activists and in which the 
organization assumes responsibility for the terrorist attack on 
a bus near the settlement of 'Ateret, north of Jerusalem, was 
disseminated in Ramallah this morning. This is the first 
operation in the framework of settling scores between the 
Palestinian people and the Zionists following the massacre in 
the Cave of the Patriarchs, the PFLP activists state in their 
leaflet. Our forces will not cease their activities until a 
just and comprehensive solution has been found to the 
Palestinian problem and until a Palestinian state with holy 
Jerusalem as its capital has been founded. The leaflet goes on 
to say that the attack was carried out by two PFLP fighters who 
succeeded in escaping. [passage omitted] 
  Two Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] terrorists were 
arrested this morning several hundred meters north of the Erez 
checkpoint. Armed with a knife, the two managed to make their 
way out of the Gaza Strip without permits to enter Israel. They 
planned to carry out a terrorist attack in Israel. They were 
carrying a leaflet signed by Hamas and a copy of the Koran. 

</TEXT>

