<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Citing Resistance sources, our security 
correspondent has reported that at 1235 today, the Resistance 
detonated an explosive device in a Mercedes car belonging to the 
Israeli intelligence as it drove along the 
al-Jarmaq-al-'Ayshiyah road. According to the same sources, the 
device killed everyone inside the car. 
  Security sources reported that two explosive devices went 
off. The first went off on the al-Jarmaq-al-'Ayshiyah road 
targeting an Israeli military vehicle. The second targeted a 
foot patrol on the al-'Ayshiyah-al-Rayhan road. Using field 
artillery, the Israeli army shelled the al-Nabatiyah-Kafr Rumman 
area. The shelling also targeted Iqlim al-Tuffah, in particular 
the Mlita and al-Luwayzah hills, from the al-Zaffatah positions. 
Israeli warplanes also overflew the area. [passage omitted] 

