people who are already in custody to issue the necessary remand 
orders against them. 
  Sources close to the investigation have revealed that 
several 
individuals now in custody have residence permits abroad and 
regularly moved between Lebanon and these other countries under 
various aliases, using forged passports of several 
nationalities. They used to enter Lebanon avoiding the official 
entry points, in fishing boats, via tourist areas, or by 
boarding Lebanese vessels on the high seas. 

