</HEADER>

<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   24 March 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> WEST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chairman of Solidarity Committee With Kurdistan Murdered </TI></H3>
<H4>   Foreign Mission Members Suspected </H4>
<F P=102> NC2403215994 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 2000 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2403215994 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] It is possible that persons connected to a foreign 
delegation in Nicosia are behind the murder of Theofilos 
Yeoryiadhis, according to the chairman of the Committee for 
Solidarity with Kurdistan. 
  Investigators are examining this possibility as they 
evaluate 
specific evidence and information. These people previously 
stayed in a European capital and were expelled for their 
participation in terrorist acts. According to evidence and 
information passed on to the Cypriot authorities, these people 
acted on the instructions of the Turkish secret service. 
  As part of the investigation, police today searched houses 
of 
foreigners in Nicosia. Furthermore, police are examining 
yellow, left-hand drive Mercedes cars to see whether one is the 
automobile driven by a foreigner who was asking for information 
on Thoukidhidhou Street, where Yeoryiadhis' family lives. 
According to evidence and eyewitness descriptions, police are 
searching for a man between 30 and 35 years old who is 
apparently the perpetrator of the cold-blooded murder. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

