<H3> <TI>   Four Foreigners Arrested Near Bombed Mosque in Nicosia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1903123994 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1000 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1903123994 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This afternoon, police will bring to Nicosia 
District Court four foreign students who were arrested late last 
night in the yard of Omeriye Mosque in Nicosia. [see item 
NC1603200294 in previous Terrorism Report] The four are 
Salah-al-Din Billu from Syria, (Usuani Uushtag) from Pakistan, 
(Larren Fernandes) from India and Ghassan Muhammad from Lebanon. 
The four students had entered the yard of Omeriye Mosque in a 
stolen car, which belongs to a resident of Aradhippou village, 
with fake license plates from a motorcycle. In their possession 
police found tools used for burglaries and other items, which 
police are checking on to see if they are stolen. 

