Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Palermo-Rome Plane Blocked"] </F>
  [Text] Rome, 21 Mar (ANSA) -- The hijacker was later 
identified as Giuseppe Cizio, 67. He was reported as warning 
that no one should approach the plane, and reiterating his 
demand to talk to the press. 
  Two members of the Carabinieri police and one of the Italian 
police force were reported as being on the passenger list. 
  The plane was surrounded, at a safe distance, by large 
numbers of Carabinieri and other police, as well as 50 or so 
firemen. 
  Cizio was reported to be brandishing a package he said 
contained a hand grenade; talking with police and Meridiana 
officials on the plane radio, he is believed to have declared 
his intention to publicise an "injustice" he received in a 
recent judicial inquiry. 
  Cizio has a record of petty crime including burglary and 
"verbally assaulting a public official". 
  Rome police chief Fernando Masone was reportedly on his way 
to the airport. 

