<H3> <TI>   `Unknown Persons' Plant Bombs in Homes of Reformists </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2403122494 Tirana ATA in English 1129 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2403122494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, March 24 (ATA) -- Unknown persons have put 
explosives into several houses of the former politically 
persecuted who have taken part in the democratic changes. 
  Bashkim Kodhima, head of the Association Former Political 
Persecuted of the Saranda district branch, and Minella Boci, the 
head of the former economically persecuted and kulaks of the 
district, issued yesterday a protest note addressed to the 
Ministry of Public Order, Ministry of Justice, the National 
Information Service (SHIK), through which they urge to find the 
terrorists. 
  Mr. Kodhima and Mr. Boci blame leftist extremists to have 
done this act. 

</TEXT>

