<H3> <TI>   `Pacifist' Writer Arrested for Killing Candidate Colosio </TI></H3>
<H4>   Initial Confirmed Report </H4>
<F P=102> PA2403022794 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0145 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2403022794 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [See Selected Video Reports section for worldwide TV </F>
coverage of killing] 
  [Excerpt] We have Ubaldo Diaz of the newspaper OVACIONES, 
from Tijuana. Go ahead Ubaldo. 
  Diaz: This afternoon at 1908 Luis Donaldo Colosio, 
presidential candidate for the ruling Institutional 
Revolutionary Party [PRI], was the target of an attack. He 
apparently sustained two bullet wounds -- one in the head and 
one in the chest. The political rally was being held in the 
Lomas de Tijuana neighborhood, better known as Lomas Taurinas. 
Colosio was leading a political rally here for 3,000 persons. 
At the end of the rally, as he was leaving the podium, two 
individuals, a young person and an older one, approached him 
with pistols and managed to shoot the PRI candidate. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

